The paper deals with graph embedding algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. The focus of the paper is on direction-aware algorithms, which are designed to capture the directionality of edges in a graph. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), which deals with the analysis of social and information networks using computational methods. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel multi-objective model for learning embeddings that preserve textual features and graph context of nodes, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
